'''Katayama Shrine''' (片山神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} classified as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft}} located at Sakasita 636, {{ill|Seki Town|ja|関町|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kameyama City|ja|亀山市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
It is situated on the {{ill|Suzuka Tunnel|ja|鈴鹿トンネル|12=draft}} of {{ill|National Route 1|ja|国道1号|12=draft}}, which forms part of the border ({{ill|Prefectural Border|ja|県境|12=draft}}) between {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|12=draft}} and {{ill|Mie Prefecture|ja|三重県|12=draft}}, atop the {{ill|Suzuka Pass|ja|鈴鹿峠|12=draft}} from which one can overlook both the {{ill|Suzuka River|ja|鈴鹿川|12=draft}} flowing toward {{ill|Ise Bay|ja|伊勢湾|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Tamura River|ja|田村川|12=draft}} flowing from {{ill|Lake Biwa|ja|琵琶湖|12=draft}}. {{Sfn|阿部|2004|pages=88-93}}{{Sfn|桐村|2012|pages=117-121}}

The surrounding area is a sacred land blessed with abundant water. It is renowned as the site of the Suzuka Misogi, where the Saio ({{ill|Saio|ja|斎王|12=draft}}) en route to {{ill|Ise Grand Shrine|ja|伊勢神宮|12=draft}} once stayed to perform misogi ({{ill|Misogi|ja|禊|12=draft}}), and later became consecrated by shamanic practitioners ({{ill|Shamanic Practitioner|ja|巫覡|12=draft}}) performing purification rituals ({{ill|Purification Ritual|ja|祓え|12=draft}}). 

Within the precincts stand the monument commemorating the origin of Suzuka-ryu naginatajutsu – {{ill|Suzuka-ryu|ja|鈴鹿流|lt=Suzuka-ryu Naginatajutsu Origin|lt_ja=鈴鹿流薙刀術発生之地|12=draft}} – and a monument honoring the filial piety of Bankichi.

