'''Katayama Shrine''' (片山神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] classified as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|lt=Shikinaisha}} located at Sakasita 636, [[:en:Seki, Mie|Seki Town]], [[:en:Kameyama, Mie|Kameyama City]], [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]].

== Overview ==
It is situated on the {{ill|Suzuka Tunnel|ja|鈴鹿トンネル|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzuka Tunnel|qq=|1=Suzuka tunnel|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11649475}} of [[:en:Japan National Route 1|National Route 1]], which forms part of the border ({{ill|Prefectural Border|ja|県境|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Border|qq=|1=prefectural border|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11582641}}) between [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]] and [[:en:Mie Prefecture|Mie Prefecture]], atop the {{ill|Suzuka Pass|ja|鈴鹿峠|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzuka Pass|qq=|1=Suzuka Pass|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11649485}} from which one can overlook both the [[:en:Suzuka River|Suzuka River]] flowing toward [[:en:Ise Bay|Ise Bay]] and the {{ill|Tamura River|ja|田村川|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamura River|qq=|1=Tamura River|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q17172424}} flowing from [[:en:Lake Biwa|Lake Biwa]]. {{Sfn|阿部|2004|pages=88-93}}{{Sfn|桐村|2012|pages=117-121}}

The surrounding area is a sacred land blessed with abundant water. It is renowned as the site of the Suzuka Misogi, where the Saio ([[:en:Saiō|Saio]]) en route to [[:en:Ise Shrine|Ise Grand Shrine]] once stayed to perform misogi ([[:en:Misogi|Misogi]]), and later became consecrated by shamanic practitioners ({{ill|Shamanic Practitioner|ja|巫覡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shamanic Practitioner|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 巫|1=Wu|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3687892}}) performing purification rituals ({{ill|Purification Ritual|ja|祓え|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Purification Ritual|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 祓|1=harae|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q3127244}}). 

Within the precincts stand the monument commemorating the origin of Suzuka-ryu naginatajutsu – {{ill|Suzuka-ryu|ja|鈴鹿流|lt=Suzuka-ryu Naginatajutsu Origin|lt_ja=鈴鹿流薙刀術発生之地|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzuka-ryu|qq=|1=Suzuka-ryū‎|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11649496}} – and a monument honoring the filial piety of Bankichi.

